  "title": "A Highway Just Turned Into a River of Beer",
  "script": "A highway full of beer? A tractor-trailer flipped on Route 44 in Salisbury, Connecticut just before dawn on Monday, and its entire load went with it. Not boxes. Not lumber. Thousands of cans of Bud Light and Michelob Ultra, rolling across both lanes like a beer avalanche. Connecticut State Police shut the highway down completely — not for the wreck, but for the flood of cans nobody could safely drive over. Crews spent hours shoveling, sweeping, and hauling away what one local outlet called a hot mess made of cold ones. No injuries, just a highway that smelled like a frat house for half a day. Somewhere, a beer distributor is doing very upsetting math right now. So who's cleaning up Route 44 tonight?",
